ISLAMABAD, July 25 (APP): Foreign Secretary Asad Majeed Khan on Tuesday reaffirmed Pakistan’s commitment to vigorously follow the objectives of the “Engage Africa” initiative and to increase trade, investment, tourism and people-to-people contacts.
The foreign secretary held a roundtable discussion with the envoys of the African Union here, Foreign Office Spokesperson posted on her Twitter handle.
